I agree wholeheartedly with Jason Snell&rsquo;s comment on page-turn buttons in his review of the latest Kindle Oasis&nbsp;&mdash;
 People will tell you that it&rsquo;s just fine to find a grip that lets you slide a finger over to the screen, tap, and then slide back every single time you turn the page. Sure, it&rsquo;s fine. But this is way better.
 When my Paperwhite broke, I started using my old Kindle again &mdash; it&rsquo;s so old it has a physical keyboard &mdash; and immediately appreciated how much better buttons work to change pages.
